5 years. 16 Diabeauties. Creating Waves.

I am going to get soft here because these 16 individuals deserve the absolute world and have truly changed my life. 

On November 1, 2017, my dream and goal came to fruition after plotting about it for 4 years prior! I inducted my first ever @DahlgrensDiabeauties in Humboldt, Saskatchewan! The crowd cheered loudly as they dropped the puck and my heart absolutely screamed with joy (🥹). That was the goal, to make the Diabeauty feel uplifted, special, beautiful, and celebrated for their difference - not alienated or looked down upon. Starting with a pregame meal at Johnnys Bistro, to wearing the Diabeauties jersey, ceremonial face-off, watching the game, meeting post game to connect & answer questions, being in a Facebook group with other like minded Diabeauties, and having a presentation at the school about T1D - I thought I was impacting them…

Fast track to November 1, 2022 and we hit the 5 year anniversary!!

What I learned throughout this process is that these young individuals living with #T1D had an immeasurable impact on me and are are some of the coolest people I’ve ever met in my entire life!! 

They inspire me daily and are doing things I never even imagined when I was at their age. 

These things include (going to brag here) - writing books & childrens novels, presenting to schools/organizations/members of parliament, creating care packages for newly diagnosed, having a skate-a-thon, summer camps, having their own programs, supporting other diabetic initiatives, creating awareness, raising funds, stepping outside of their comfort zone, succeeding academically & athletically & artistically, being a genuine kind hearted human, leaders in life, team captains, and never letting #TypeOneDiabetes stop them from pursuing their dreams… which leaves me speechless and beyond proud. 

Each one has created waves in their own unique way that will ripple for generations! 

I’m just grateful to be along for the ride of their life and support the Diabeauties family on their endeavours. 

Love you all dearly & Happy 5 years ❤️💛 

Major thank you for all the support that made this what it is today! #DD16

Coming into 2023, I had a conversation with a good friend of mine who asked - “What is your word for 2023?”

I took a few seconds to think and the first word that came to my head was…

Enrichment - “The action of improving or enhancing the quality or value of something. Enrichment of the soil for more plant growth."

I want to enrich the lives of those who are around me. My next door neighbour. Communities I enter. Strangers I see on the street or in the subway. I want to enrich through action, connection, smiles, gestures, words, sharing, educating, empathy, kindness, love, and choosing to be the best version of myself everyday so that each encounter I have would make the situation a little bit better!

Not only others, but enrich myself with health, connections, knowledge, experiences, adventures, taking risks, challenges, learning, growth, and enlightenment. It’s the small details and the finer things in life that mean the most to me - not the richest or most expensive things. I don’t even care about that, which makes it more of a paradox that my word is enrichment.

See, we all have our off days and make mistakes, me included. But if we could enrich the lives of those around us - we help alleviate those tough days and uplift others. 

You have a New Year’s resolution? Then let’s crush it and I’ll support you on that journey! You want to step outside of your comfort zone or break free from something toxic in your life? For sure and I’ll be cheering in your corner, life’s too short to stay put in something unhealthy or things you’re not passionate about!! Don’t get caught one step behind worrying if you’re not sure you can succeed, you will never know unless you give it your best shot! 

I’d love to hear what your word is for 2023 in the comments below! Let’s have the best year yet 🫶

2 years ago on this day I took a major leap out of my comfort zone unveiling much of my story I had never shared before.

During this time, I felt such a mix of emotions. Felt raw, which made me present. Was exposed, but not naked. Completely open, yet so healed. My heart was racing, but I also felt so at ease. 

See I had let go of the fear of what others might think of me. Put all the “what ifs” to the side. Surrendered the thoughts of what “could have been” and “should have been”.

I channelled my energy to focus on the things I can control and used the story of my first 22 years in this world to create a positive impact. I gave my all into something that will last eternity and it was the most alive I had ever felt. 

What has transpired since this day has been a whirlwind of love, support, encouragement, connections, growth, and experiences of a lifetime. Sharing my story through writing, speeches, and all forms has presented me with the opportunity to learn and be inspired by others on their journeys throughout life. I learned that through sharing my story, I found inspiration in hearing other peoples stories and connecting on a level that goes far beyond the surface.

I am truly grateful for all the things that have happened in my life because they have made me the person I am today. I am not perfect, nobody is, but I sure am human! 

Much love to you all and thanks for enjoying the grind along with me 💛💙 #MyCrossroads

What are you doing for your brain health? 🧠 

This is a question I get asked often since I live with a severe traumatic brain injury (TBI) and Brain Injury Awareness Month is next month! To answer, I do A LOT since our brain is arguably the most important organ of our body!! 

One thing I started in November of 2022 is called Brain Echo Therapy! This is a new technology and is just starting to make waves in Canada! The therapy is ran by @insightfullving in Barrie, ON and is one of only two locations in Canada (other is in Calgary, AB). 

Before starting, I was heavily dependent on supplements/vitamins to improve my brains function. After receiving Brain Echo sessions, I really struggled and went down a brain functioning spiral - not being able to focus, lack of energy, memory issues, insomnia, and not doing well in school. After a month, I started to get back to my normal self, but without the supplements and thriving even better than I did before! 

To nerd out, my brain was in a sympathetic state (fight or flight) and I wasn’t able to regulate efficiently between my bodies autonomic sympathetic/parasympathetic states - sacrificing more energy and not replenishing it as effectively while sleeping. Brain Echo let my brain look at itself to increase efficiency and help regulation through new neuropathways (we generate 9000 new ones daily). 

Professionals in all fields have been seeking this therapy to help their Traumatic Brain Injury/Concussion, Post-Covid symptoms, brain fog, PTSD, depression, anxiety, insomnia, stress, ongoing preventative of brain health decline, and several other conditions.

I personally found great benefit working with Debbie and suggested my parents do it as well since they both have demanding schedules in long term care facilities! We all had major improvements, received delicious meals as part of treatment, learned new things, created healthy habits, and are happy with our own experience! 

I do many things behind the scenes to maintain my health, so I wanted to bring awareness to a technology that made an impact on my loved ones. I hope this can help others as much as it’s helped my family & I ❣️

#ad This summer, I’ve travelled from coast to coast. While that sounds incredible and amazing, I also must carefully and thoughtfully plan how I manage my diabetes. My Dexcom G6 CGM System* has been a game changer and given me more flexibility and peace of mind with its accurate glucose level readings. ​
​
But that’s not even the best part! Even though I’m in different provinces, my friends and family can still stay connected to me through Dexcom’s Follow app‡. It gives them more peace of mind too when they can worry less about me and live more in the moment while taking in Canada’s beautiful scenery. 🌄 @dexcomcanada​
​
*To be sure this product is suitable for you, always read and follow the instructions on the labelling. Back of upper arm wear is available for users 18 years and older.​​
† For a list of compatible devices, go to www.dexcom.com/compatibility.​
‡ Following requires the use of the Follow app and an Internet connection. Followers should always confirm readings on the Dexcom G6 app before making diabetes treatment decisions​
​
#LifewithDexcom #DexcomWarrior

For National Diabetes month, the team at @OmnipodCA asked me, “Who’s just my type?”; meaning, someone that motivates me in the diabetes community! It wasn’t an easy choice because every single person in the community motivates me to spread awareness and positivity around living with type 1 diabetes. First off, I thought about my @dahlgrensdiabeauties and how incredible they all are in their own special ways. Also, my diabetes mentors, friends living with type 1 diabetes, professionals in all different areas of the world doing incredible things with type 1 diabetes, and this man… Dr. Michael Riddell!

I chose Dr. Riddell because he took me under his wing at York University when I first moved to Toronto, and I don’t feel like he gets nearly enough recognition outside the world of diabetes for all that he does! Some of his work includes: 

- 200 published peer-reviewed journal articles
- Authored 30 book chapters and several international health guidelines 
- Created a diabetes patient guidebook, 
- Has presented over 500 scholarly talks and keynotes, 
- AND is listed in the Stanford University list of the top 2% of cited researchers in the World

@RiddellMichael22 you’re #justmytype because you go above and beyond to increase the research, education, awareness, and understanding of diabetes to the entire world. You are a true trailblazer and it’s an honor to call you my good friend. I look forward to making more memories together! 

A challenge for everyone else - Who’s #justyourtype?
